> One thing does still not clear for me - should we keep old behavior with a switch (-UseWindowsPowerShellConverter)?

@iSazonov Do not change any of the existing `ConvertTo-Json` code. Instead, implement another `ConvertTo-Json` in a separate class, say`ConvertToJsonCommand2`. Then apply `ExperimentalFeatureAttribute` to both `ConvertToJsonCommand` and `ConvertToJsonCommand2` just like the following:

```
[ExperimentalFeature("NewConvertToJson", ExperimentAction.Hide)]
[Cmdlet("ConvertTo", "Json", ....)]
public class ConvertToJsonCommand : PSCmdlet { ... }

[ExperimentalFeature("NewConvertToJson", ExperimentAction.Show)]
[Cmdlet("ConvertTo", "Json", ....)]
public class ConvertToJsonCommand2 : PSCmdlet { ... }
```
